♪No longer fear broken trust♪

7
00:00:55,680 --> 00:01:02,140
♪Mother, I've grown up♪

8
00:01:02,480 --> 00:01:05,420
♪No longer try♪

9
00:01:05,810 --> 00:01:09,910
♪To fill every void♪

10
00:01:10,080 --> 00:01:13,680
♪No longer saddened♪

11
00:01:13,700 --> 00:01:17,430
♪By all the goodbyes♪

12
00:01:17,430 --> 00:01:21,020
♪No longer blame♪

13
00:01:21,350 --> 00:01:24,660
♪Love that led nowhere♪

14
00:01:24,660 --> 00:01:28,860
=HER=

15
00:01:29,660 --> 00:01:32,580
=Episode 22=

16
00:01:35,380 --> 00:01:36,250
Sorry, Lady.

17
00:01:36,500 --> 00:01:37,850
- What?
- You're on the blacklist.

18
00:01:38,780 --> 00:01:39,810
You don't remember me?

19
00:01:39,810 --> 00:01:41,020
You must leave now.

20
00:01:41,020 --> 00:01:43,380
We will not let you in,
even if anyone comes.

21
00:01:44,140 --> 00:01:45,530
David is my friend.

22
00:01:45,530 --> 00:01:46,970
I'm sorry, you must leave.

23
00:01:49,170 --> 00:01:50,020
David!

24
00:01:50,020 --> 00:01:51,310
- You must leave.
- David...

25
00:01:55,660 --> 00:01:57,410
Hello, what's up?

26
00:01:57,970 --> 00:01:58,970
Hello, Jiang Fang.

27
00:01:58,970 --> 00:02:00,090
I'm home now.

28
00:02:00,290 --> 00:02:02,260
I'm starving. When will you be back?

29
00:02:02,530 --> 00:02:04,500
I'm buying groceries
right now.

30
00:02:04,500 --> 00:02:05,340
Just wait a bit.

31
00:02:05,780 --> 00:02:07,530
Boss, I ordered pork belly.

32
00:02:07,530 --> 00:02:08,810
What kind of meat is this?

33
00:02:09,010 --> 00:02:10,540
It's too fatty. How do I eat this?

34
00:02:11,340 --> 00:02:13,010
Alright, I'll head back soon.

35
00:02:13,010 --> 00:02:14,020
Just wait at home.

36
00:02:19,820 --> 00:02:22,140
When I have money,
I won't even come here if you invite me.

37
00:02:24,180 --> 00:02:25,050
Right here!

38
00:02:30,180 --> 00:02:31,210
Waiting for me, huh?

39
00:02:31,660 --> 00:02:32,930
That's so sweet of you.

40
00:02:42,060 --> 00:02:43,770
Quite a splurge, Zan.

41
00:02:45,010 --> 00:02:47,060
When you were young,
you loved these egg tarts.

42
00:02:47,060 --> 00:02:47,900
Remember that?

43
00:02:47,900 --> 00:02:49,010
Yeah, I remember.

44
00:02:49,010 --> 00:02:49,850
This tastes amazing.

45
00:02:49,850 --> 00:02:51,180
So amazing.

46
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:53,900
Let's head home. It's boiling out.

47
00:02:53,900 --> 00:02:54,770
Let's eat at home.

48
00:02:56,620 --> 00:02:57,740
Go on without me.

49
00:02:58,340 --> 00:02:59,740
I'm taking the bus to school.

50
00:03:02,780 --> 00:03:03,650
What's up?

51
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:04,700
You're not coming with me,

52
00:03:04,730 --> 00:03:05,770
you little sneak?

53
00:03:06,290 --> 00:03:07,180
No.

54
00:03:08,530 --> 00:03:10,090
I used to think it was your fault.

55
00:03:10,250 --> 00:03:12,210
Now I think it's
actually Liu Yan's fault.

56
00:03:12,690 --> 00:03:13,650
She isn't very sharp.

57
00:03:14,100 --> 00:03:15,300
You're totally gaslighting her.

58
00:03:16,620 --> 00:03:17,460
What?

59
00:03:18,220 --> 00:03:19,060
English?

60
00:03:19,460 --> 00:03:20,740
Go wherever you want.

61
00:03:21,530 --> 00:03:23,260
I'm warning you one last time.

62
00:03:24,940 --> 00:03:26,540
Stay away from Liu Yan.

63
00:03:27,130 --> 00:03:28,650
That's your own daughter.

64
00:03:29,850 --> 00:03:30,740
Jiang Fang,

65
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:32,890
try being a decent person.

66
00:04:16,490 --> 00:04:17,780
Here's your appetizer.

67
00:04:17,900 --> 00:04:19,580
It's an otoro

68
00:04:19,580 --> 00:04:20,930
and caviar tartare.

69
00:04:20,930 --> 00:04:22,610
On top is finger lime.

70
00:04:22,610 --> 00:04:23,580
And underneath

71
00:04:23,580 --> 00:04:25,100
is the wild yeast seeded bread

72
00:04:25,100 --> 00:04:26,900
we introduced earlier.

73
00:04:26,900 --> 00:04:28,340
It's sliced thin

74
00:04:28,340 --> 00:04:29,740
and baked into crisps.

75
00:04:30,290 --> 00:04:31,180
Eat it in one bite.

76
00:04:31,470 --> 00:04:32,940
Making things so classy now?

77
00:04:33,250 --> 00:04:34,090
Wait, hold on.

78
00:04:36,090 --> 00:04:36,930
Take your time.

79
00:04:36,930 --> 00:04:37,810
Okay, okay.

80
00:05:08,050 --> 00:05:09,250
Turn up the heat to reduce the sauce.

81
00:05:09,290 --> 00:05:10,180
Yes, Chef!

82
00:05:10,610 --> 00:05:13,020
Each piece must be 0.5 centimeters.

83
00:05:13,020 --> 00:05:13,940
- All right?
- Okay.

84
00:05:14,700 --> 00:05:16,260
Is this 0.5 centimeters?

85
00:05:16,260 --> 00:05:17,370
After each cut,

86
00:05:17,370 --> 00:05:18,530
you should check yourself

87
00:05:18,530 --> 00:05:19,700
if it's 0.5 centimeters.

88
00:05:19,700 --> 00:05:20,570
Okay, got it.

89
00:05:20,730 --> 00:05:21,610
No problem.

90
00:05:21,850 --> 00:05:22,740
Don't worry about it.

91
00:05:23,900 --> 00:05:25,660
Daxiang, the lobster
is almost ready soon.

92
00:05:25,660 --> 00:05:27,100
Add a bit of baijiu.

93
00:05:27,100 --> 00:05:28,700
- Yes, Chef!
- After you add baijiu,

94
00:05:28,700 --> 00:05:30,020
serve it directly on the board.

95
00:05:30,020 --> 00:05:30,860
Yes, Chef!

96
00:05:30,860 --> 00:05:31,930
Everyone, speed up.

97
00:05:31,930 --> 00:05:32,780
Hurry up!

98
00:05:32,930 --> 00:05:33,900
Yes, Chef!

99
00:05:41,820 --> 00:05:43,370
Jiang Fang showed up so suddenly.

100
00:05:44,460 --> 00:05:46,540
I'm afraid she might trick you.

101
00:05:47,290 --> 00:05:49,690
Things are good
between me and Jiang Fang now.

102
00:05:50,020 --> 00:05:51,730
- Are you sure?
- She has changed this time

103
00:05:51,730 --> 00:05:52,850
and quit gambling for good.

104
00:05:52,850 --> 00:05:54,010
Don't worry anymore.

105
00:05:54,660 --> 00:05:55,540
Really.

106
00:05:57,050 --> 00:05:57,930
Salty...

107
00:06:05,140 --> 00:06:07,570
Why are you so fussy?

108
00:06:08,850 --> 00:06:09,970
Aside from Jiang Fang,

109
00:06:09,970 --> 00:06:13,140
is everything else okay?

110
00:06:13,140 --> 00:06:14,010
Yeah, it's all good.

111
00:06:14,530 --> 00:06:15,420
What's up?

112
00:06:15,820 --> 00:06:16,660
Nothing, really.

113
00:06:16,660 --> 00:06:18,130
I'm just asking.

114
00:06:18,730 --> 00:06:20,180
You haven't dated anyone before.

115
00:06:20,340 --> 00:06:21,780
In a foreign land,

116
00:06:21,850 --> 00:06:22,700
I'm afraid

117
00:06:22,700 --> 00:06:24,660
you might get hurt by men.

118
00:06:24,780 --> 00:06:26,100
Alright, stop nagging, let's go.

119
00:06:26,900 --> 00:06:28,780
If you keep nagging,
the plane will take off.

120
00:06:30,970 --> 00:06:31,860
I'm leaving.

121
00:06:39,080 --> 00:06:39,970
I'll go.

122
00:06:39,970 --> 00:06:40,840
Bye.

123
00:06:41,100 --> 00:06:42,410
If you don't reply to my messages,

124
00:06:42,410 --> 00:06:43,300
I'll come over again.

125
00:06:43,300 --> 00:06:44,720
Alright, got it.

126
00:06:56,170 --> 00:06:57,930
It's packed cleaner
than a moving company.

127
00:06:59,970 --> 00:07:00,970
Sold everything

128
00:07:00,970 --> 00:07:01,930
except the tables and chairs?

129
00:07:01,930 --> 00:07:03,010
Look down on them, huh?

130
00:07:05,550 --> 00:07:06,490
What about the little turtle?

131
00:07:07,370 --> 00:07:08,250
What did you say?

132
00:07:08,900 --> 00:07:09,900
Little turtle.

133
00:07:23,050 --> 00:07:24,300
She even sold the car?

134
00:07:34,100 --> 00:07:34,970
My relationship

135
00:07:34,970 --> 00:07:36,010
with Jiang Fang needs to change.

136
00:07:36,820 --> 00:07:38,340
Since you already think that way,

137
00:07:38,660 --> 00:07:40,340
I think it's better

138
00:07:40,340 --> 00:07:41,260
to seize this chance

139
00:07:41,260 --> 00:07:43,220
to send her
to the gambling addiction center.

140
00:07:54,660 --> 00:07:55,540
Lu Tianchi,

141
00:07:57,020 --> 00:07:58,250
I need to tell you something.

142
00:08:03,220 --> 00:08:04,140
I think I have to move

143
00:08:04,140 --> 00:08:05,100
to Highland to live.

144
00:08:05,700 --> 00:08:07,570
Highland is about to earn diamonds soon.

145
00:08:07,900 --> 00:08:09,610
I'm the sous chef now.

146
00:08:10,050 --> 00:08:11,860
The chefs are still recovering.

147
00:08:12,460 --> 00:08:14,220
I need to help out more.

148
00:08:15,730 --> 00:08:17,220
Weren't we talking about your mom?

149
00:08:17,220 --> 00:08:18,780
How did we switch to Highland?

150
00:08:18,780 --> 00:08:20,560
Can't you work from here, too?

151
00:08:23,460 --> 00:08:25,210
Neither of us has a car now.

152
00:08:26,100 --> 00:08:28,380
If I live here,
I have to take the bus every day.

153
00:08:28,650 --> 00:08:30,050
It's too much time wasted.

154
00:08:32,420 --> 00:08:34,180
But if you're not living at home,

155
00:08:34,180 --> 00:08:36,930
the evidence of cohabitation

156
00:08:37,100 --> 00:08:38,130
we need to collect

157
00:08:38,130 --> 00:08:39,730
won't be enough.

158
00:08:40,490 --> 00:08:42,020
Mr. He said on the way

159
00:08:42,650 --> 00:08:44,500
that Highland Group will guarantee me.

160
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:46,660
They'll bring me in as a special talent.

161
00:08:47,220 --> 00:08:48,660
It should be approved.

162
00:08:50,650 --> 00:08:52,420
So, if it's not necessary,
let's not proceed.

163
00:08:52,420 --> 00:08:53,260
Right?

164
00:08:53,610 --> 00:08:54,970
We've put in so much effort.

165
00:08:55,970 --> 00:08:56,850
Lu Tianchi,

166
00:08:59,460 --> 00:09:00,460
during my temple visit,

167
00:09:00,460 --> 00:09:02,020
I figured out a lot.

168
00:09:02,580 --> 00:09:03,420
I came to Gaya

169
00:09:03,420 --> 00:09:04,690
to find Jiang Fang.

170
00:09:05,420 --> 00:09:06,780
Now I stay here

171
00:09:07,290 --> 00:09:09,180
because I have other things
to accomplish.

172
00:09:09,540 --> 00:09:10,420
So,

173
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:12,210
is earning diamonds

174
00:09:13,420 --> 00:09:15,380
really that important to you?

175
00:09:17,540 --> 00:09:18,650
Or is there someone else

176
00:09:18,650 --> 00:09:20,140
who matters more to you?

177
00:09:21,250 --> 00:09:22,090
Let's discuss this

178
00:09:22,090 --> 00:09:23,660
another day when we have time.

179
00:09:26,250 --> 00:09:28,180
I really don't have time lately.

180
00:09:30,580 --> 00:09:31,940
Can you regularly help send

181
00:09:31,940 --> 00:09:33,690
some food to Wang Daxiang's mom?

182
00:09:34,050 --> 00:09:35,580
No one's looking after her these days.

183
00:09:37,770 --> 00:09:38,970
I'll go pack my things first.

184
00:10:08,100 --> 00:10:09,540
Lu Tianchi, are you leaving?

185
00:10:11,100 --> 00:10:12,620
No, just getting some air.

186
00:10:13,940 --> 00:10:15,180
I'll take you to Highland later.

187
00:10:49,940 --> 00:10:50,810
Lu Tianchi,

188
00:10:50,810 --> 00:10:51,770
(Liu Yan)

189
00:10:51,770 --> 00:10:52,690
thanks for everything.

190
00:10:54,300 --> 00:10:55,180
Good night.

191
00:11:09,010 --> 00:11:09,900
Liu Yan?

192
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,550
- Why are you here?
- Why are you here?

193
00:11:13,850 --> 00:11:15,140
What brings you here?

194
00:11:15,490 --> 00:11:16,540
I'm here for work.

195
00:11:17,010 --> 00:11:18,940
No, I mean,

196
00:11:18,940 --> 00:11:20,080
why so early,

197
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:20,940
Mr. He?

198
00:11:20,940 --> 00:11:22,500
I come at this time every day.

199
00:11:23,010 --> 00:11:24,180
What time is it now?

200
00:11:24,180 --> 00:11:25,050
It's 5 AM?

201
00:11:25,890 --> 00:11:27,490
Mr. He, do you ever sleep?

202
00:11:27,490 --> 00:11:28,490
Come on, get up now.

203
00:11:28,490 --> 00:11:29,460
Put your clothes on.

204
00:11:29,460 --> 00:11:30,780
Don't sleep on the floor here.

205
00:11:31,420 --> 00:11:32,300
Alright.

206
00:11:40,540 --> 00:11:41,420
Mr. He,

207
00:11:41,940 --> 00:11:43,570
this is Highland Group's hotel.

208
00:11:43,730 --> 00:11:44,680
It's close to the restaurant.

209
00:11:44,890 --> 00:11:46,370
You should stay here for now.

210
00:11:46,370 --> 00:11:47,420
No need, Mr. He.

211
00:11:47,420 --> 00:11:48,780
This is the chef's order.

212
00:11:49,100 --> 00:11:50,210
It's not up for discussion.

213
00:11:54,370 --> 00:11:55,260
Thank you.

214
00:11:58,890 --> 00:12:00,540
I have a question for you.

215
00:12:01,370 --> 00:12:02,260
Go ahead.

216
00:12:03,250 --> 00:12:04,140
I think,

217
00:12:05,060 --> 00:12:06,820
besides assisting the head chef

218
00:12:06,820 --> 00:12:08,090
in making great food,

219
00:12:09,130 --> 00:12:10,730
the sous chef should also

220
00:12:11,540 --> 00:12:13,330
handle team management, right?

221
00:12:13,690 --> 00:12:14,530
Right.

222
00:12:14,530 --> 00:12:16,300
A sous chef is like glue,

223
00:12:16,300 --> 00:12:18,060
always in touch with the staff,

224
00:12:18,060 --> 00:12:19,180
such as interacting

225
00:12:19,180 --> 00:12:21,100
and communicating with the staff.

226
00:12:21,100 --> 00:12:22,060
So the kitchen can be

227
00:12:22,060 --> 00:12:23,850
a cohesive place. Isn't that right?

228
00:12:23,850 --> 00:12:25,100
Highland is very cohesive.

229
00:12:25,100 --> 00:12:27,180
Chef, I think our kitchen

230
00:12:27,180 --> 00:12:28,330
isn't about cohesion.

231
00:12:28,540 --> 00:12:29,540
It's fear.

232
00:12:30,380 --> 00:12:31,740
Everyone is scared of you.

233
00:12:34,250 --> 00:12:36,310
Sous Chef, watch your words.

234
00:12:36,850 --> 00:12:37,730
Well,

235
00:12:38,940 --> 00:12:40,130
during my temple visit,

236
00:12:40,130 --> 00:12:41,730
I figured out a lot.

237
00:12:41,730 --> 00:12:42,620
For example?

238
00:12:42,770 --> 00:12:44,540
For example, earning Three Diamonds

239
00:12:44,820 --> 00:12:46,260
takes a ton of hard work.

240
00:12:46,820 --> 00:12:48,180
But it's not just about cuisine.

241
00:12:48,890 --> 00:12:50,660
Since you made me sous chef,

242
00:12:50,820 --> 00:12:51,700
I really want to take

243
00:12:51,700 --> 00:12:52,900
this responsibility seriously.

244
00:12:54,300 --> 00:12:55,660
So how do you plan to do that?

245
00:12:56,180 --> 00:12:57,300
I think the kitchen should

246
00:12:57,300 --> 00:12:58,420
have its own set of rules.

247
00:12:58,480 --> 00:12:59,610
Even if you're the head chef,

248
00:12:59,610 --> 00:13:01,500
you can't break rules or cheat.

249
00:13:02,300 --> 00:13:03,260
What do you mean?

250
00:13:10,460 --> 00:13:11,900
Is this really pasta?

251
00:13:12,180 --> 00:13:13,780
Does pasta have toppings?

252
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,720
Kind of the toppings
for noodles with soybean paste.

253
00:13:15,820 --> 00:13:17,140
Have you eaten that?

254
00:13:17,340 --> 00:13:18,340
Yeah, I'm from the north.

255
00:13:18,340 --> 00:13:19,660
Pasta with toppings?

256
00:13:20,080 --> 00:13:20,970
Noodles with soybean paste?

257
00:13:23,460 --> 00:13:24,660
- Smells so good.
- That's it.

258
00:13:24,770 --> 00:13:26,340
I have a few words to say.

259
00:13:26,340 --> 00:13:27,220
Before,

260
00:13:27,220 --> 00:13:28,540
I wasn't confident in myself,

261
00:13:28,540 --> 00:13:30,300
so I often lost my temper.

262
00:13:30,300 --> 00:13:32,060
I didn't consider everyone's feelings.

263
00:13:32,060 --> 00:13:33,010
Today, I want

264
00:13:33,010 --> 00:13:34,260
to sincerely apologize.

265
00:13:38,420 --> 00:13:39,890
Today's staff meal was cooked by me.

266
00:13:39,890 --> 00:13:41,330
Eat well to work well.

267
00:13:41,330 --> 00:13:42,180
Right.

268
00:13:42,180 --> 00:13:43,200
So, starting today,

269
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:45,180
working on an empty stomach
will result in a pay deduction.

270
00:13:45,180 --> 00:13:46,580
Every night before service,

271
00:13:46,580 --> 00:13:47,890
let's all eat together.

272
00:13:47,890 --> 00:13:49,650
And to make this meal

273
00:13:49,650 --> 00:13:50,770
more enjoyable,

274
00:13:50,770 --> 00:13:52,060
I think we should

275
00:13:52,060 --> 00:13:53,140
change the music.

276
00:13:53,650 --> 00:13:54,540
Change the music?

277
00:13:55,970 --> 00:13:57,090
Will Mr. He allow it?

278
00:13:57,770 --> 00:13:59,930
We've listened to this for years.

279
00:14:00,420 --> 00:14:01,350
Do we really need a new one?

280
00:14:01,370 --> 00:14:02,210
Time to eat!

281
00:14:03,850 --> 00:14:04,890
Alright, let's eat.

282
00:14:04,890 --> 00:14:06,730
- Some manners, please.
- Everyone's ready.

283
00:14:06,940 --> 00:14:07,810
Hand it to me.

284
00:14:08,610 --> 00:14:09,690
Shake before eating.

285
00:14:14,370 --> 00:14:15,260
Mr. He.

286
00:14:16,540 --> 00:14:17,900
Beijing noodles with soybean paste.

287
00:14:19,370 --> 00:14:20,590
What's that music outside?

288
00:14:21,820 --> 00:14:22,690
It's for the noodles.

